## Planning Loop (CEO CODEX ↔ CLAUDE CODE)

```
CEO writes REQ → Claude writes PLAN → CEO reviews
  Round 1: GO or REVISE
  Round 2: GO or REVISE
  Round 3: GO or CANCEL (MUST decide, no round 4)
```

CEO says WHAT and WHY. Claude decides HOW. No implementation hints in REQ.

## Execution Loop (CLAUDE CODE ↔ CODEX REVIEW)

```
Claude executes + commits → Codex Review reviews diff
  Fix attempt 1 (if NEEDS-REVISION)
  Fix attempt 2 (if still NEEDS-REVISION)
  Surgical fix or HARD-NO (if still failing after 2 attempts)
```

Surgical fix: 1 file, ≤20 lines, specific issue only. Not refactoring.

## Anti-Loop Guarantees

| Counter | Max | On Max Hit |
|---------|-----|------------|
| Plan versions | 3 | GO or CANCEL |
| Execution fixes | 2 | Surgical fix or HARD-NO |
| Surgical fixes per task | 1 | HARD-NO if fix fails |
| Total lifecycle rounds | 7 | REQ + 3 plan versions + execute + 2 fix attempts |

## Verdicts

- **GO**: no critical findings, acceptance criteria met → merge
- **NEEDS-REVISION**: medium findings, criteria partially unmet → file:line feedback
- **HARD-NO**: critical flaw → BLOCKED, escalate to human
- **CANCEL**: task removed by CEO → may split and re-issue
- **GOOD-ENOUGH**: surgical fix applied → ship, log in hindsight

